gmailieer (1.1-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * New upstream version
    - re-branded from “gmailieer” to “lieer”
    - new option: --file-extension
    - set Maildir message mtime to Gmail internalDate (for sorted ls!)
    - many minor bug fixes
  * Bump to policy 4.5.0, no changes required
  * Bump to debhelper 12
  * Secure debian/copyright format URL
  * Set upstream metadata fields: Repository, Repository-Browse.
  * Update git-buildpackage configuration
  * Add requires-root field to debian/rules
  * Update debian/watch to version=4
  * Bump debhelper from old 12 to 13.

 -- Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>  Fri, 17 Apr 2020 15:47:56 +0100

gmailieer (0.10-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream version; highlights:
    - only allow one instance of gmi for each directory using fcntl.lockf()
    - allows syncing categories (personal, social, etc)
    - various improvements in batch sizing
    - do not use progressbar if not tty

 -- Julian Andres Klode <jak@debian.org>  Mon, 22 Oct 2018 13:26:44 +0200

